1. Which part of Terraform is responsible for managing the lifecycle of
resources and building the dependency graph?
ANS : terraform core
Terraform internal architecture and component responsibilities.
Terraform is built around a core engine and a plugin-based architecture. Terraform
Core is responsible for interpreting configuration files, creating the resource
dependency graph, and managing the lifecycle of resources. Providers are separate
plugins that define resource types and communicate with external service APIs,while
state and backends focus on tracking and storing infrastructure data rather than
controlling execution logic.
