2. What is the primary function of a Terraform provider?
A. Storing the state file in a secure cloud location
B. Managing the user authentication for the Terraform Cloud website
C. Encrypting the sensitive data stored in local variables
D. Understanding API interactions and exposing resources for a specific service
Purpose and function of Terraform providers :
Providers enable Terraform to interact with specific platforms and services by
implementing the required API calls. They define available resources and data sources
and translate Terraform configurations into actions that external systems can
understand. Without providers, Terraform would not be able to create or manage
infrastructure in cloud or third-party services.
